# Installation Guide

## For End Users (using the tool)

### Quick start (no install needed)
  npx cc-optim

### Global install
  npm install -g cc-optim
  cc-optim

### Prerequisites
  - Node.js >= 18
  - npm >= 9

### What cc-optim installs in your project
  - repomix (devDependency) — Codebase packaging for LLMs
  - grov (devDependency) — Persistent session memory for Claude Code

  These are saved to your package.json so anyone cloning the repo
  gets them automatically via `npm install`.

---

## For Developers (contributing to cc-optim)

### Setup
  git clone https://github.com/tbk-ai-systems/cc-optim.git
  cd cc-optim
  npm install

### Build
  npm run build          # Bundles src/ → dist/index.js via tsup

### Test locally
  npm link               # Makes `cc-optim` available globally
  cd /tmp/test-project   # Go to any project
  npm init -y            # Create a minimal project
  cc-optim               # Run the TUI

### Development mode
  npm run dev            # Rebuilds on file changes (tsup --watch)

### Type checking
  npm run typecheck      # Runs tsc --noEmit
